news.title: Transindia Real Estate to sell its logistics park in Jhajjar for Rs 636.71 crore
news.para: Transindia Real Estate has divested its 10% stake held in Malur Logistics & Industrial Parks, Venkatapura Logistics & Industrial Parks, Kalina Warehousing, Panvel Warehousing, and Allcargo Logistics & Industrial Park, for an equity consideration of near Rs 4.55 crore.

news.title: Britain's Taylor Wimpley to build fewer houses in 2024 amidst limited supply
news.para: The British housebuilder said its first-half operating profit margin would reflect slightly lower pricing in the homes it has coming through, citing cost inflation and investment.

news.title: Hong Kong agents say property deals jump after big policy moves
news.para: Hong Kong, long among the world's most expensive housing markets, saw prices plunge 20% from their 2021 peak, hurt by the pandemic, an exodus of residents triggered by Beijing's imposition of the national security law and interest rate hikes.

news.title: Making construction sites safer with AI technology
news.para: In general, through diverse AI forms, including machine learning and deep learning, construction companies can accurately identify risks faster, monitor real-time progress, detect potential hazards and make informed decisions to address issues in the construction process.

news.title: Holcim posts profit of 1.12 billion Swiss francs in Q4 2023
news.para: The Swiss cement maker, which last month announced plans to spin off its fast-growing American business, was in confident mood after posting record annual operating profit on the back of efficiency gains and price increases.

news.title: Home building permits in Germany dips 27% in 2023
news.para: Some 260,100 permits were issued, which is 94,100 fewer permits than in 2022 and the lowest since 2012, The number of building permits is an important indicator of future construction.

news.title: Jharkhand government to probe irregularities in allotment of houses
news.para: Gomia MLA of Ajsu-P Lambodar Mahto raised the issue in the house and alleged that gram sabha has been sidelined and officials are preparing list of beneficiaries in violation of all the prescribed rules. He also cited a few examples.

news.title: Around 5,000 buildings flout holding tax norms: Bhubaneswar civic body
news.para: Around 5,000 residential holdings in Bhubaneswar are being used for commercial purposes, resulting in the loss of tax revenue for Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation (BMC).

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram civic body's council approves draft master plan 2040
news.para: This was one of the key recommendations in the draft master plan of the city corporation. It has been decided to apply the Kerala Municipality building rules for the construction of any type of building.

news.title: Delhi civic body seals five more shops under sealing drive in Connaught place
news.para: An NDMC official said that on Tuesday five shops were sealed but two were desealed later. In one case, a payment was made. In another, a court order was given.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body council to discuss about property tax hike on Feb 29
news.para: At the phone-in programme organised at the Mayor’s chamber on Wednesday, a caller from Bejai said that the property tax under SAS has been hiked by 70%. Last year, the property tax was Rs 11,836.

news.title: Telangana government waives off 90% interest on accumulated property tax arrears
news.para: The waiver is applicable to both private and government properties within the Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation (GHMC) limits as well as other ULBs under the ‘One Time Scheme’ (OTS).

news.title: Odisha government to allot houses to poor in Pahala area
news.para: The houses were built under Model I of the Housing for All Policy of the state govt wherein the private developers got govt land at a subsidised rate to build their housing project and in return they reserve 10% of the housing units for the EWS people.

news.title: Consumer forum fines Vennala-based interior design firm
news.para: The complainant had assigned Bright Maintenance Company for interior design works for his house in Jan 2021, As per the agreed terms, the complainant shifted to another house paying a rent of Rs 35,000.

news.title: Survey proposes to bring all properties in Mangaluru under tax net
news.para: Presenting the budget, Varun Chowta, chairman of the standing committee for taxation, finance and appeals, said the total receipts, including the opening balance, is estimated at Rs 1,113.4 crore.

news.title: Ahmedabad: As heritage TDR scheme crawls, many trapped in crumbling homes
news.para: Their home at Hanlla pol, off Relief Road, has major structural weaknesses. It is among the 76 Unesco-listed world heritage houses that were “approved” by the civic body for repairs.

news.title: Trichy civic body completes 78 projects under smart cities mission
news.para: Major projects such as multi-level car parking (MLCP), renovated fish markets, and public parks have already been completed. However, other projects funded by the smart cities mission received an extension until March 2024.

news.title: Unauthorised offices of real estate agents built on YEIDA plots, razed
news.para: These land parcels were originally allotted to two builders whose land allocations were canceled a few years ago due to their failure to initiate construction and fulfill their financial obligations to the Authority.
